Change Log

From version 1.0.2 to 1.1.0

- Support large chunk size that is a multiple of 4KB. Note that we do not
  support some file sizes for a file being written to NCFS. Please refer to
  the user guide for details.
- The configuration is now stored in XML format.
- A standalone recovery utility is now used to support the recovery operation.
  See the user guide for details. 
- Bugs have been fixed.

From version 1.0.1 to 1.0.2

- Updated MBR coding scheme to support generic (n,k) MDS property. The type
  number for this scheme is still 1000.
- Added a generic Reed-Solomon coding scheme which supports generic (n,k) MDS
  property. The type number for this scheme is 3000.

From version 1.0.0 to 1.0.1

- Renamed CodingStorageLayer class to CodingLayer class.
- Renamed DiskLayer class to StorageLayer class.
